        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:58PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 457 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
New Preston, or 10 miles north of New Milford, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Corner Of The Pines, Cornwall, Grappaville, Haight Vineyard, Kent
Furnace, North Corners, West Goshen, Skiff Mountain, Lower Merryall,
Warren, Marble Dale, Tyler Lake Heights, Kent Green, Cornwall Bridge,
Preston Hill, North Kent, Northfield, Kellogg Corners, Calhoun
Corners, and Morris.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
